<h2 id="the-code">The code</h2>

<p>In the HTML we simply add the number to a span with the class of <code class="highlighter-rouge">.number</code>.</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>&lt;p class="text-green"&gt;&lt;span class="number"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="text-green"&gt;&lt;span class="number"&gt;550001&lt;/span&gt; total&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="text-green"&gt;¬£&lt;span class="number"&gt;845&lt;/span&gt; spent&lt;/p&gt;
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>For the JS side we take each element using the  <code class="highlighter-rouge">.number</code> class and we pass that to the JS snippet. We then perform some simple math on the content of the element and step up until we reach the target number.</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>function countUp(numberElement) {
  let current = 0;
  const total = parseInt(numberElement.textContent);
  const increment = Math.ceil(total / 100);

  function step() {
    current += increment;
    if (current &gt; total) current = total;
    numberElement.textContent = current.toLocaleString();
    (current !== total) &amp;&amp; requestAnimationFrame(step);
  }
  step();
}

document.querySelectorAll('.number').forEach(elem =&gt; countUp(elem));
</code></pre></div></div>

